# Production VM Access

The CarWatch production server runs on an Oracle Cloud VM.

- **IP:** 129.159.142.247
- **User:** ubuntu
- **SSH key:** ~/Downloads/ssh-key-2026-04-20.key
- **App dir:** /home/ubuntu/carwatch
- **Config:** /home/ubuntu/carwatch/config.yaml
- **Domain:** carwatch.duckdns.org

## Quick SSH

```bash
ssh -i ~/Downloads/ssh-key-2026-04-20.key ubuntu@129.159.142.247
```

## Makefile targets

All `make vm-*` targets use the defaults above automatically:

- `make vm-ssh` — interactive shell
- `make vm-logs` — tail container logs
- `make vm-restart` — restart the container
- `make vm-status` — show container status
- `make vm-deploy` — pull and recreate the container
